{"lemma":"خَلَّةٌ","slug":"خَلَّةٌ","root":"خ.ل.ل","root_slug":"خ-ل-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ل-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"خَلَّةٌ","root":"خلل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n11169"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"gap, perforation, breach, gap even in canes or as large as a road"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dearth, need"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"peculiar trait, disposition, property","examples":[{"text":"الجُوذابات. أمّا المعمولة منها بالخبز فغذاؤها غذاء محمود والدم المتولّد منه دم جيّد لأنّها معمولة من خبز نضيج، وهي ملينة للطبيعة نافعة من خشومة قصة الرئة. وإن كانت باللبن والسكّر وماء النارجيل وعلّقت عليها بطّة سمينة أو دجاجة سمنة زادت في الباه زيادةً كثيرةً. والمعمولة بالحنطة غليطة بطيئة الهضم حارّة معطشة، والمعمولة بالأرزّ دونها في هذه الخلال. وكلّها كثير الغذاء بطيء النزول، ينبغي أن يستعان على هضمها بطول النوم وأن لا تؤكل هي إلا على جوعٍ صادق.","english":"al-jūḏābāt. When made from bread they are a laudably sustaining sustenance furthering the blood production for they are made from well-baked bread, and they are laxative and help against roughness of the windpipe, and if they are prepared with milk and sugar and coconut water and a fat duck or fatty chicken is hung above them then they add much to the libido. And made with wheat they are tough, slow in digestion, hot and causing thirst, whereas made with rice they are below these amiable properties. And all of them are sustaining and going down slowly; it is desired that one supports their digestion with long sleep and does not eat them except upon real hunger."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cordiality, amity, true friendship, affection","examples":[{"text":"يَا أَيُّهَا ٱلَّذِينَ آمَنُوا أَنْفِقُوا مِمَّا رَزَقْنَاكُم مِن قَبْلِ أَن يَأْتِيَ يَوْمٌ لَا بَيْعٌ فِيهِ وَلَا خُلَّةٌ وَلَا شَفَاعَةٌ","english":"O ye who believe! spend of that wherewith We have provided you ere a day come when there will be no trafficking, nor friendship, nor intercession. – Pickthall"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"an opaque term used for any plant which is not حَمْض (ḥamḍ, “any saline, mostly a chenopodiaceous or zygophyllaceous plant”)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lace, toothpick, and the like instruments for picking"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"scabbard, case, wherewith for instance a sword is covered, and a thong fixed onto the extremity of a bow"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"toothpickweed, Ammi gen. et spp."}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From خَلَّ (ḵalla, “to penetrate”). The Bedouinic term may be instead from خَلّ (ḵall, “vinegar”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n11169","headword_ar":"خَلَّةٌ","root":"xl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A road between two roads."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A hole, perforation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bore, that penetrates,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passes through, a thing, and is small:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a general sense:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a gap,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"breach, in a booth of reeds"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"canes."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalalN","text_ar":"خَلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  [And hence,] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gap that is left by a person who has died:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, T, S, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place, of a man, that is left vacant after his death."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) One says, of him who has lost a person by death,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aall~`hum~a A@xolufo EalaY A^aholihi bixayorK waA@sodudo xal~atahu","text_ar":"اَللّٰهُمَّ ا@خْلُفْ عَلَى اَهْلِهِ بِخَيْرٍ وَا@سْدُدْ خَلَّتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O God, supply to his family, with that which is good, the place of him whom they have lost,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and fill up the gap which he has left by his death."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, T, S, * TA.) ―         -b4-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"interval,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inter-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":780},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vening space, between the piercer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thruster, and the pierced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thrust:"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqaEa","text_ar":"رَقَعَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xal~apa AlfaArisi","text_ar":"خَلَّةَ الفَارِسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", explained in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rqE","text_ar":"رقع"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O and K and TA in that art.) ―         -b5-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Want,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a want: poverty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"need, straitness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"difficulty."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi xal~apN $adiydapN","text_ar":"بِهِ خَلَّةٌ شَدِيدَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has pressing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"severe, need"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"straitness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"difficulty."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~a A@ll~`hu xal~atahu","text_ar":"سَدَّ ا@للّٰهُ خَلَّتَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God supply his want."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And it is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxal~apu tadoEuw A_ilaY Als~al~api","text_ar":"الخَلَّةُ تَدْعُو اـِلَى السَّلَّةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Want invites to theft."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaSolapN","text_ar":"خَصْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (JK, S, Mgh, Msb, K;) both signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A property, quality, nature,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disposition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a habit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"custom:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL, PS, TK:) [and app. also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a practice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an action:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] in a man: (TA: [see the latter word:]) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xilaAlN","text_ar":"خِلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (JK, Mgh, Msb, K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xal~atuhu HasanapN","text_ar":"خَلَّتُهُ حَسَنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one, his nature,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disposition, is good"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IDrd, TA.) And hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayoru xilaAli","text_ar":"خَيْرُ خِلَالِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~aAy^imi Als~iwaAku","text_ar":"الصَّايِمِ السِّوَاكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The best of the habits,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"customs, of the faster is"},{"kind":"text","text":"the use of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the tooth-stick"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xul~apN","text_ar":"خُلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An isolated tract of sand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"separate from other sands."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haDobapN","text_ar":"هَضْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An elevated tract of sand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but more commonly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hill;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a spreading mountain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (JK, TA.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) in a general sense: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sour, wine:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wine altered for the worse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in flavour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without acidity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sourness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) pl. [or coll. gen. n.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xal~N","text_ar":"خَلٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xal~N","text_ar":"خَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence.       -A5-  And see this last word near the end of the paragraph, in four places."}],"source_refs":["K","As","T","S","TA","KL","PS","TK","Fr"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}